00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:18.076
(Laughter)

00:08:18.100 --> 00:08:20.196
And I think the imagination
is the only limit

00:08:20.220 --> 00:08:21.976
of what you can think of

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.476
when this kind of technology
merges with real life.

00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:26.376
But many of you argue, actually,

00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:29.076
that all of our work is not
only about physical objects.

00:08:29.100 --> 00:08:32.076
We actually do lots
of accounting and paper editing

00:08:32.100 --> 00:08:34.391
and all those kinds of things;
what about that?

00:08:34.415 --> 00:08:37.976
And many of you are excited
about the next-generation tablet computers

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:39.976
to come out in the market.

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:41.976
So, rather than waiting for that,

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:44.976
I actually made my own,
just using a piece of paper.

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:47.000
So, what I did here
is remove the camera --

00:08:47.024 --> 00:08:50.976
All the webcam cameras have
a microphone inside the camera.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:53.976
I removed the microphone from that,

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:55.976
and then just pinched that --

00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:58.976
like I just made a clip
out of the microphone --

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:02.976
and clipped that to a piece of paper,
any paper that you found around.

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:05.976
So now the sound of the touch

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:08.976
is getting me when exactly
I'm touching the paper.

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:12.976
But the camera is actually tracking
where my fingers are moving.

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.976
You can of course watch movies.

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:18.976
(Video) Good afternoon.
My name is Russell,

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:21.976
