00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:36.000
(Applause)

00:09:37.396 --> 00:09:40.174
Many of you already must have
thought, OK, you can browse.

00:09:40.198 --> 00:09:42.476
Yeah. Of course you can
browse to any websites

00:09:42.500 --> 00:09:45.176
or you can do all sorts
of computing on a piece of paper

00:09:45.200 --> 00:09:46.376
wherever you need it.

00:09:46.400 --> 00:09:48.976
So, more interestingly,

00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:51.976
I'm interested in how we can
take that in a more dynamic way.

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:54.976
When I come back to my desk,
I can just pinch that information

00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:56.976
back to my desktop

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:59.976
so I can use my full-size computer.

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:01.976
(Applause)

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.976
And why only computers?
We can just play with papers.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:07.976
Paper world is interesting to play with.

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:09.976
Here, I'm taking a part of a document,

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:13.976
and putting over here a second part
from a second place,

00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:18.976
and I'm actually modifying the information
that I have over there.

00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:23.976
Yeah. And I say, "OK, this looks nice,
let me print it out, that thing."

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:26.381
So I now have a print-out of that thing.

00:10:26.405 --> 00:10:28.729
So the workflow is more intuitive,

00:10:28.753 --> 00:10:31.976
the way we used to do it
maybe 20 years back,

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:34.976
rather than now switching
between these two worlds.

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:37.976
So, as a last thought,

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:42.376
I think that integrating
information to everyday objects

00:10:42.400 --> 00:10:45.976
will not only help us to get rid
of the digital divide,

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:47.976
the gap between these two worlds,

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:49.976
but will also help us, in some way,

00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:51.976
to stay human,

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:55.000
to be more connected
to our physical world.

00:10:58.408 --> 00:11:00.976
And it will actually help us
not end up being machines

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:02.718
sitting in front of other machines.

00:11:03.507 --> 00:11:05.976
That's all. Thank you.

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:19.976
(Applause)

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:21.176
Thank you.

00:11:21.200 --> 00:11:23.976
